SampleDescription.Description: Metaphase and interphase FISH studies using probes within these regions (RP11-641K4, RP11-110D2, RP11-136O17, and 2q subtelomere probe, respectively) confirmed these rearrangements and demonstrated that they are likely the result of a complex rearrangement of chromosome 2 resulting in a terminal deletion and inverted duplication/triplication of the adjacent region of the q-arm.
